Incorporate advanced metrics like Value at Risk (VaR) and Conditional VaR (CVaR). 1. Value at Risk (VaR): Measures potential loss over a given time frame with a confidence level (ğ›¼): \[
VaR_{\alpha} = Percentile_{(1-\alpha) \cdot 100}(R_{t}^{Portfolio})
\] 2. Conditional Value at Risk (CVaR): Average loss beyond the VaR threshold: \[
CVaR_{\alpha} = E[R_{t}^{Portfolio} | R_{t}^{Portfolio} \leq VaR_{\alpha}]
\]


Show the code
#  Financial Analysis
# Value at Risk (VaR)
def calculate_var(returns, confidence_level=0.95):
      return np.percentile(returns, (1 - confidence_level) * 100)
# Conditional Value at Risk (CVaR)
def calculate_cvar(returns, confidence_level=0.95):
      var = calculate_var(returns, confidence_level)
      return returns[returns &lt;= var].mean()

var = calculate_var(portfolio_returns, 0.95)
cvar = calculate_cvar(portfolio_returns, 0.95)
print("Value at Risk (95%):", var)
print("Conditional Value at Risk (95%):", cvar)


